er Currents within Rastafari Thought and the Adoption of a Feminist Agenda in the Rasta Women's Movement |journal=Agenda: Empowering Women for Gender Equity |volume=7 |issue=57 |year=2003 |pages=76\u201383 |jstor=4066393 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite journal |first=Alemseghed |last=Kebede |year=2003 |title=Projective Framing, Cultural Opportunity Milieu, and the Rastafari |journal=Sociological Focus |volume=36 |issue=4 |pages=353\u2013370 |doi=10.1080/00380237.2003.10571229 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite journal |first=Alemseghed |last=Kebede |year=2001 |title=Decentred Movements: The Case of the Structural and Perceptual Versatility of the Rastafari |journal=Sociological Spectrum |volume=21 |issue=2 |pages=175\u2013205 |doi=10.1080/02732170118234 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite journal |first=Stephen A. |last=King |year=1999 |title=The Co-optation of a \"Revolution\": Rastafari, Reggae, and the Rhetoric of Social Control |journal=Howard Journal of Communications |volume=10 |issue=2 |pages=77\u201395 |doi=10.1080/106461799246834 |ref=|url=https://thekeep.eiu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1014&context=commstudies_fac }}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Lake |first=Obiagele |title=Rastafari Women: Subordination in the Midst of Liberation Theology |year=1998 |publisher=Carolina Academic Press |isbn=978-0890898369 |ref= |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/rastafariwomensu0000lake }}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Lee |first=H\u00e9l\u00e8ne |title=First Rasta: Leonard Howell and the Rise of Rastafarianism |year=2004 |publisher=Chicago |isbn=978-1556525582 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Murrell |first=Nathaniel Samuel |title=Tuning Hebrew Psalms to Reggae Rhythms: Rastas' Revolutionary Lamentations for Social Change |journal=CrossCurrents |volume=50 |number=4 |year=2001 |pages=525\u2013540 |jstor=24460879 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Niaah |first=Jahlani |title=Poverty (Lab) Oratory: Rastafari and Cultural Studies |year=2003 |journal=Cultural Studies |volume=17 |issue=6 |pages=823\u2013842